# Rust
/target/
**/*.rs.bk
# Cargo.lock is intentionally tracked: sqz/sqz-mcp are binary crates, so
# committing the lockfile keeps builds reproducible (including offline
# CI builds that rely on the cached, locked dependency graph).

# IDE
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp
*.swo
*~

# OS
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Node (npm/extension builds)
node_modules/
dist/
out/
*.vsix

# Python
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.egg-info/
build/

# SQLite databases (test artifacts)
*.db
*.db-journal
*.db-wal
*.db-shm

# Proptest regression files are checked in intentionally
# sqz_engine/proptest-regressions/

# Environment
.env
.env.local

# Cargo packaging
*.crate

# Build artifacts
sqz-source.zip
.audit-external/

# Generated rustdoc (rebuilt + published by .github/workflows/docs.yml)
docs/doc/

# sqz init outputs (created when testing sqz in its own workspace).
# These are meant to be written into USER projects that install sqz,
# not into sqz's own source tree. They contain machine-specific paths.
#
# Note: .claude/, .clinerules/, .gemini/, opencode.json are already
# tracked in this repo from older sqz dev iterations. They're not
# ignored here so you can still see changes to them. If you want them
# gone, delete and commit the removal separately.
.cursor/
.windsurfrules
# AGENTS.md is generated by `sqz init` for Codex (issue #-follow-up:
# Codex integration). Same machine-specific-path concern as .cursor/:
# the block sqz installs contains absolute paths to the local sqz
# binary, so it's not portable across contributor machines.
AGENTS.md
# CLAUDE.md is generated by `sqz init` for Claude Code MCP guidance.
# Contains machine-specific paths to the local sqz binary.
CLAUDE.md

# Kiro hooks generated by `sqz init` contain absolute paths to the local
# sqz binary and are not portable across contributor machines.
.kiro/
# Arbor AST code map
.arbor/
